metadata.abstract: The document titled 'Familiarisation' provides a comprehensive overview of familiarisation sessions conducted across various Flight Information Regions (FIRs) in Germany. It includes detailed tables listing the sessions held in EDGG (Langen FIR), EDMM (Munich FIR), and EDWW (Bremen FIR). Each table entry specifies the session ID, the FIR where the C1 CPT was done, and whether a familiarisation session was conducted in other FIRs. The document is structured to facilitate easy reference and tracking of familiarisation activities, ensuring that controllers are well-acquainted with the operational procedures and airspace management in different regions. This information is crucial for maintaining high standards of air traffic control and ensuring seamless coordination across FIRs.
